news.title: MahaRERA can decide payout for mental agony to flat buyers
news.para: The order was passed on a complaint by Sanjay and Shailaja Gaikwad who sought not only direction to Omkar Realtors and Developers to hand over possession of the flat and to pay interest for delayed possession, but also Rs 2 crore compensation for the “mental torture and agony” caused to them.

news.title: Gurugram: 21 unauthorised houses sealed in Sushant Lok-1
news.para: Similarly, developers of seven illegal colonies, spread over 35 acres of agricultural land, were served notices by the enforcement wing of DTCP for violations of the Urban Area Act.

news.title: Faridabad: Conman arrested for duping over 500 people in land fraud
news.para: Joint commissioner (EOW) Chhaya Sharma said the accused, Sudhir Bidhuri (38), was a resident of Tughlaqabad. He started off as a small-time property dealer and later joined a reality firm and started duping people.

news.title: Tata, Siemens group consortium to develop Pune metro line 3
news.para: The 23.3-km elevated metro line connects the Hinjewadi Rajiv Gandhi Infotech Park with Shivajinagar via Balewadi in the second largest city in Maharashtra.

news.title: Haryana to launch portal to analyse hourly air pollution data from C&D sites in January
news.para: The portal, with video fencing with remote connectivity and a live dashboard for easy monitoring, will be operational within a week, said HSPCB secretary S Narayana.

news.title: J&K government sign MoUs worth Rs 18,900 crore with builders
news.para: Manoj Sinha, Lieutenant Governor of Union Territory of Jammu and Kashmir predicted that it is likely to receive close to Rs 60,000 crore of investment in real estate sector in very near future since the government has top priority to transform this sector which would have multiplier effects on the UT's economy.

news.title: China Evergrande reports progress in resuming home deliveries
news.para: Company chairman Hui Ka Yan stressed during a meeting on Sunday that no one at Evergrande would be allowed to "lie flat", urging employees to fight day and night so that sales can be resumed and debts repaid, Evergrande said in a statement.

news.title: Karnataka imposes curbs on sale of small agri plots to rein in illegal residential layouts
news.para: The Revenue department has taken the step to curb sale of such plots as housing sites by unscrupulous developers as the practice has led to haphazard growth of urban areas with total disregard to planning and aesthetics, limiting the government's ability to provide infrastructure in such areas.

news.title: RLDA to lease land parcel in Ludhiana at Rs 108 crore
news.para: The area of the site spans across 25,257.67 square metre while the area to be leased is around 21185.54 square metre. The proposed site has excellent connectivity to the major transportation centers of the city.

news.title: Hyderabad: 2BHK projects lack access to basic services
news.para: In the pilot assessment of the affordable housing schemes carried out by the CSE, it was also pointed out that there is still considerable scope of reducing heat gain in buildings, improving ventilation and day-lit areas to improve thermal comfort and reduce energy intensity of structures.

news.title: Emami Realty surges 10% on CARE's rating upgrade
news.para: Speaking about the prospects of the realty sector in West Bengal, Managing Director and Chief Executive Officer Nitesh Kumar, earlier this month, expressed optimism, saying that the extension of the window for stamp duty reduction had benefited the real estate environment on the whole.

news.title: SICMA requests FM to facilitate movement of cement from southern states to deficit regions
news.para: South India, with 180 Million Tonnes Per Annum (MPTA) capacity accounts for almost 40 per cent of the India's cement production and 35-40 per cent of limestone was also found in the southern parts of the country.

news.title: Office leasing to grow by 30–35% in 2022 : Experts
news.para: “Overall, we estimate net absorption to rebound strongly, recording a 30–35% growth to reach 29–31 million square feet (msf) levels by the end of 2022, in line with the decadal average,” said Badal Yagnik, managing director - tenant representation, Cushman & Wakefield. “Overall, the office story is looking very promising in the year ahead.”

news.title: Stuck registries of flats in Noida may inflate EMI for homebuyers
news.para: The bank notices have cited delay in registry of flats as the reason. They have referred to certain conditions mentioned in the sanction letter that was signed between the buyer and the bank during the disbursement of home loans.

news.title: NCLT directs Indiabulls Real Estate to discuss Embassy merger with shareholders
news.para: This is the last hurdle to be cleared by the company for the proposed merger that would result in Indiabulls Group’s complete exit from real estate business and a reverse listing for Embassy.
